# set-being-llm.word — the calling being sets its OWN llm configuration (llm-assigner/ops.js
# set-being-llm DO op). MULTI-MOMENT composite (the writeLlmFields fan-out, now words): the 7-step
# chain fields (slot list, force flags, preferOwn) each land as their OWN do:set-being fact on the
# caller's being reel — one moment per field, exactly as the old handler's per-field doVerb loop.
#
# WORD-SOLE (handler-less, Tabor's no-mirror law): this `.word` is the ONLY path (do.js
# runOpWordToStore runs it via runWordToStore, so each deed seals its own moment; runAsStore). The
# host see resolve-llm-config is the floor — legacy-normalize (connectionId → connections), the
# force-flag mutex, slot-name validate, resolve the target (the caller's being), and BUILD the
# { field, value } write list. It lays NO fact; the deeds lay the facts. Mode "being".
#
# The bridge binds `target`, `params`, `caller`, `branch`.

When a being sets its own llm configuration:
  If no caller, refuse with "set-being-llm requires an authenticated being." as unauthorized.
  see resolve-llm-config(params, caller) as cfg.
  For each w in cfg's writes:
    do set-being on the being $cfg.targetId with { field: $w.field, value: $w.value, merge: false } as wrote.
  Return beingId: $cfg.targetId.
